  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5f7201a12d95ffc409449d95f23cf332, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 0.19607843, g: 0.19607843, b: 0.19607843, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 10102, guid: 0000000000000000e000000000000000, type: 0}
    m_FontSize: 22
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 0
    m_MaxSize: 40
    m_Alignment: 4
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: " 1 : RES PEN is the RES PEN of the character. Ex :  Seele in her improved
    state gain 20 % Quantum RES PEN. \n 2 :  The BASE DEF of ennemy is 200 + (10
    * Ennemy Level). \n 3 :  The Universal Damage Reduction Multiplier is 100% when
    the ennemy toughness is equal to 0 and 90% when not. \n 4 : The Extra Multiplier
    is reserved for some character like Dang Heng with Slowed ennemy. \n 5 : Only
    few character can influence the Weaken Multiplier therefore in in most cases
    this Multiplier is equal to 100%. \n 6 : Due to the use of commas there is an
    error up to 0.10% between the damage displayed and the damage in game. \n 7 :
    If an ennemy has a weakness to the character element its RES is equal to 0. If
    it has no weakness to that element his RES is  equal to 20. If it has a RES to
    that element his RES will be equal to 40. \n 8 : Characters like Sampo or Welt
    can influence the Damage Taken Multiplier. \n 9 : Scaling Attribute is the attribute
    the skill scales off, in most cases it is ATK. \n 10 : Thanks for using this
    tool. I hope you enjoy it and you find it useful. "
